About us

MiDispensary Team

With extensive experience across a myriad of therapeutic areas and chronic conditions, as well as in-depth knowledge of the latest research and benefits of endocannabinoid support our Doctors and Nurses are here to help you.


Prioritising patient outcomes, compassionate care and offering alternative treatment options, our Doctors are brand agnostic and prescribe to best suit your individual health concerns.

Book Now
What is MiDispensary

MiDispensary is a speciality medical clinic dedicated to supporting patients seeking endocannabinoid support. Located in Sydney’s iconic Eastern Suburbs we provide telehealth appointments for patients Australia wide.

Why choose MiDispensary?

Prioritising patient outcomes, compassionate care and offering alternative treatment options for patients suffering a variety of chronic health concerns, our Doctors are brand agnostic and prescribe to best suit your specific health requirements.

How can MiDispensary help me?

Our Nurses and Doctors have extensive experience across a wide variety of health concerns. Treating patients around the nation, our practitioners are dedicated to helping patients find the most suitable treatment options for their individual requirements.

How much do consultations cost?
  • An initial consultation costs $95.00 and includes your Doctors appointment, prescriptions and a follow up consultation with one of our Nurses. If treatment is not suitable, you will be provided a full refund.
  • Follow up consultations cost $65.00 and include treatment assessment and prescription adjustments.
  • Prescriptions adjustments where a consultation is not required costs $20.00 and is limited to three prescriptions.
  • Nurse consultations are complimentary, and available to discuss your treatment plan.
  • Costs for medications are NOT included in these fees.
What is the cancellation policy?

We understand that you may not always be able to make your consultation. If you do need to reschedule or cancel, please provide a minimum of 24 hours notice. Cancellation fees of 50% apply if you cancel less than 24 hours before your appointment.

To cancel your appointment please contact us direcly at 1300 MITIME or info@midispensary.com.au

Can I reschedule my consultation?

Yes, you can reschedule up to 12 hours before your appointment. Appointments within 12 hours will need to be cancelled and rebooked, cancellation fees apply.

Do I need a referral?
Whilst a referral is not necessary, it is always welcome if available. For patients aged 50 years or younger, you don’t need a referral, simply fill in our patient intake and screening forms and book your appointment. If you are not suitable for treatment, you will be given a full refund. For some patients, a medical history may be required and we will work with you to obtain this.
How do I reschedule or cancel my consultation?

Request a cancellation by contacting our team at 1300 MITIME or at info@midispensary.com.au

Why do I need follow up consultations?
Regular follow up consultations allow your doctor to check in on your treatment progress and ensure it is having the intended effects. During these consultations, you can ask any questions you may have including discussing any changes regarding your prescriptions, as well as request script updates or adjustments.
How often will I need to see the Doctor?
During your first year of treatment you will be seen at regular intervals, as follows:
  1. Initial Consultation
  2. Fortnight Check Up
  3. 3 Month Check Up
  4. 6 Month Check Up
  5. 12 Month Check Up
Changes to this layout are not uncommon, depending on response to treatment and is at your treating Doctors’ discretion. If you have any questions regarding your treatment plan that does not require a Doctors’ consultation you can organise an appointment with one of our Nurses free of charge.
How long does my prescription(s) last?
Prescription length can vary depending on your treatment plan. Generally, prescriptions last between 3-6 months, and will have a specific number of repeats and intervals associated. If your prescription has expired and there are repeats remaining, you will be unable to use them.
What is the cost of treatment?
Medication costs vary depending on your prescriptions. However, average pricing can range between $120 to $500 per month.
What if my medication is discontinued or out of stock?
If your medication is discontinued or out of stock, you will receive a complimentary appointment to adjust your prescriptions accordingly.
Does your clinic provide open scripts?

Our clinic does not provide patients with open prescriptions as per the Therapeutic Good Administration guidelines.

What brands do MiDispensary practitioners prescribe?
Our doctors are brand agnostic. As such, if you are eligible for endocannabinoid support treatment our doctors will create a personalised treatment based on your medical history, condition and individual health concerns.
What forms of medication are available?
Many forms of endocannabinoid support medication exist, if eligible your treating Doctor will discuss these formats with you.
Do you dispense medications?

We do not currently dispense medications but we work with a number of pharmacies around the country to help you obtain your prescriptions. You can also take your prescription to a pharmacy of your choice. We will soon be opening MiPharmacy onsite at our MiDispensary Bondi Junction Clinic.
